How to choose a conference. Formulation of the title and abstract of the presentation. Writing the paper and having presented the oral presentation. Critical reflection of the presentation after the conference in the seminarObjectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce doctoral students the main types of scientific conferences, to encourage them to participate in conferences and to give practical advice how to benefit the most from one's first conferences. For completing the course it is necessary to participate in seminars and have an experience of attending a conference. The student has to send abstract of the presentation and the materials used (slides, transparencies, handouts) or full text of the presentation (depending on the type of a conference) to the lecturer. Both students who have already attended a conference or are planning to do it can participate in the seminars but credit points will be delivered only to students who have made a presentation or prepared handouts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students acquire the skills for choosing an appropriate scientific conference, compose an abstract and write the presentation. The students will be able to present the paper within the time limit.
